WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:12.000
Level 1. The Travels of Ibn Batuta. Chapter 1. The Journey Begins.

00:31.000 --> 00:50.000
My uncle, Ibn Batuta, sat by the window of his house in Tangia. It was the hot time of the day and his eyes were half open.

00:51.000 --> 00:54.000
I went into the room.

00:55.000 --> 01:03.000
Uncle, I said quietly. He looked up at me suddenly.

01:04.000 --> 01:08.000
Ah, Ahmed, it's you again.

01:09.000 --> 01:10.000
He smiled.

01:11.000 --> 01:15.000
Yes, uncle. I answered.

01:17.000 --> 01:22.000
Can you tell me today about your journeys, please?

01:23.000 --> 01:28.000
I want to travel when I'm older too, I said.

01:29.000 --> 01:30.000
Is that right?

01:31.000 --> 01:32.000
He answered.

01:33.000 --> 01:37.000
Then he looked carefully at me.

01:38.000 --> 01:40.000
How old are you now?

01:41.000 --> 01:51.000
He could remember things from long ago easily, but things from the day before, not very well.

01:53.000 --> 01:56.000
I'm eleven, I said.

01:57.000 --> 02:08.000
Well, perhaps in four or five years you can begin to travel. But it's not easy, you know.

02:09.000 --> 02:18.000
You can see wonderful towns and cities, meet interesting people, and do exciting things.

02:19.000 --> 02:30.000
But there are bad times too. You can get ill, meet big hungry animals, or lose all your money.

02:31.000 --> 02:38.000
No, I said. My eyes were big and open.

02:39.000 --> 02:40.000
Yes, Ahmed.

02:41.000 --> 02:42.000
He answered.

02:43.000 --> 02:51.000
But listen to my stories, and perhaps you too can learn to come home alive.

02:52.000 --> 02:53.000
He laughed.

02:54.000 --> 02:58.000
Now, where shall I begin?

03:00.000 --> 03:04.000
I sat down, ready to listen to him.

03:04.000 --> 03:13.000
Every time my uncle told his stories, they were different, new, and interesting.

03:14.000 --> 03:18.000
I was born here in Tangier.

03:19.000 --> 03:20.000
He began.

03:21.000 --> 03:23.000
But of course, you know that.

03:24.000 --> 03:25.000
He smiled.

03:26.000 --> 03:31.000
My father and his father before him were judges.

03:32.000 --> 03:36.000
So, I learnt to be a judge too.

03:37.000 --> 03:44.000
When you're a judge, it's easy to travel. You're important, you see.

03:45.000 --> 03:48.000
Yes, I said.

03:49.000 --> 03:54.000
Perhaps I can be a judge too one day.

03:55.000 --> 03:58.000
Perhaps, he smiled.

03:59.000 --> 04:07.000
My first journey was a pilgrimage to the holy city of Makka.

04:08.000 --> 04:18.000
I got on a donkey and said goodbye to my mother and father in Tangier when I was 21.

04:19.000 --> 04:21.000
My mother cried.

04:21.000 --> 04:30.000
After Sunday's journey, I came to the town of Algiers.

04:31.000 --> 04:39.000
Here, I met more pilgrims, and we travelled to the city of Constantine.

04:40.000 --> 04:43.000
I met the rich ruler there.

04:44.000 --> 04:52.000
He looked at my dirty old coat, smiled, and gave a beautiful new coat to me.

04:53.000 --> 04:56.000
Why? I asked.

04:57.000 --> 05:01.000
Good men help people when they need it.

05:03.000 --> 05:09.000
After some days, I left Constantine with the other pilgrims.

05:10.000 --> 05:14.000
We never stopped moving because we were afraid.

05:15.000 --> 05:21.000
Perhaps, people could take our money from us when we slept, we thought.

05:23.000 --> 05:29.000
I was soon ill, and I wanted to go to bed and die.

05:30.000 --> 05:36.000
But my friends put me on my old donkey and hit the animal from behind

05:36.000 --> 05:39.000
to make it go quickly down the road.

05:40.000 --> 05:43.000
Did you want to come home then, uncle?

05:44.000 --> 05:45.000
Of course.

05:46.000 --> 05:47.000
He smiled.

05:48.000 --> 05:50.000
But I journeyed to Tunis.

05:51.000 --> 05:54.000
The good traveller doesn't stop easily.

05:55.000 --> 05:59.000
I left Tunis in a caravan of pilgrims.

06:00.000 --> 06:05.000
They asked me, can you be the judge in our caravan?

06:07.000 --> 06:09.000
Of course, I said, yes.

06:10.000 --> 06:15.000
A caravan judge. Not bad work for a young man.

06:17.000 --> 06:22.000
When our caravan arrived in Alexandria, I was excited.

06:23.000 --> 06:26.000
I wanted to see the famous pharaohs there.

06:28.000 --> 06:31.000
I know, I said quickly.

06:32.000 --> 06:36.000
That's a big lighthouse from long ago.

06:37.000 --> 06:39.000
Did you go up it?

06:40.000 --> 06:42.000
No. He laughed.

06:43.000 --> 06:45.000
The pharaohs was in ruins.

06:46.000 --> 06:48.000
There wasn't a lot to see.

06:49.000 --> 06:52.000
But not far from Alexandria.

06:53.000 --> 06:55.000
I met a holy man.

06:56.000 --> 07:01.000
Burhan Adim. He could see into the future.

07:03.000 --> 07:05.000
And what did he tell me?

07:06.000 --> 07:10.000
You're going to visit India and China.

07:11.000 --> 07:16.000
And on your travels, you're going to meet many old friends.

07:18.000 --> 07:20.000
I was happy about this.

07:21.000 --> 07:24.000
I'm going to go far, I thought.

07:25.000 --> 07:30.000
And did you go to India and China in the end?

07:31.000 --> 07:33.000
Wait and see, Ahmed.

07:34.000 --> 07:36.000
Smiled my uncle.

07:37.000 --> 07:43.000
I arrived in Cairo, eight months after I first left home.

07:44.000 --> 07:46.000
What a big city.

07:47.000 --> 07:49.000
And what a lot of people.

07:50.000 --> 07:55.000
And they never stop running here and there, day and night.

07:57.000 --> 08:00.000
And near Cairo, there are the pyramids.

08:01.000 --> 08:06.000
Big old buildings from the rulers of Egypt long ago.

08:07.000 --> 08:11.000
And were they in ruins? I asked.

08:12.000 --> 08:15.000
No, not the pyramids.

08:16.000 --> 08:17.000
He smiled.

08:18.000 --> 08:22.000
Next, I journeyed up the river Nile.

08:23.000 --> 08:28.000
After this, we traveled on camels through the hot desert.

08:29.000 --> 08:32.000
There were lots of hungry hyenas there.

08:33.000 --> 08:36.000
And at night, we needed to be very careful.

08:37.000 --> 08:40.000
Of course, I cried excitedly.

08:41.000 --> 08:47.000
One night, a big hyena came and took everything from my bag.

08:48.000 --> 08:49.000
He said.

08:50.000 --> 08:52.000
But we soon left the desert.

08:53.000 --> 09:01.000
Then, I traveled to the holy city of Jerusalem and visited the famous buildings there.

09:03.000 --> 09:05.000
Next, I went to Damascus.

09:06.000 --> 09:08.000
What a beautiful city.

09:09.000 --> 09:14.000
Then, I traveled to Arabia and visited Medina.

09:15.000 --> 09:19.000
And in the end, I arrived in Mecca.

09:20.000 --> 09:27.000
After a year and a half, it was wonderful to arrive in the city of my pilgrimage.

09:28.000 --> 09:32.000
I learnt from holy men there and prayed for three weeks.

09:33.000 --> 09:38.000
And, did you come back home then? I asked.

09:39.000 --> 09:40.000
No.

09:41.000 --> 09:49.000
Every night, I thought of the holy man Burhan Agdin and of India and China.

09:50.000 --> 09:56.000
I was a true traveler now, and I didn't want to stop.

09:57.000 --> 10:03.000
So, I left Mecca with the ruler of Persia's caravan.

10:04.000 --> 10:11.000
When I was young, I heard many stories about the wonderful towns near there.

10:12.000 --> 10:17.000
But on my journey, I saw something very different.

10:18.000 --> 10:22.000
Years before, the Mongols came to these towns.

10:23.000 --> 10:30.000
They killed a lot of people, and I saw many houses in ruins there.

10:32.000 --> 10:38.000
Perhaps the most interesting town on that journey was Wasit.

10:39.000 --> 10:45.000
A number of men with no money lived there in a big house.

10:46.000 --> 10:51.000
In the evening, they prayed and ate their dinner.

10:52.000 --> 10:57.000
Then they sat near a big fire and told stories.

10:58.000 --> 11:03.000
Suddenly, some of them walked into the fire.

11:04.000 --> 11:07.000
Then, they ate the fire.

11:08.000 --> 11:14.000
One man put a snake's head in his mouth and ate it alive.

11:16.000 --> 11:21.000
And you saw all that? I cried.

11:22.000 --> 11:23.000
Yes.

11:24.000 --> 11:25.000
He laughed.

11:26.000 --> 11:30.000
I visited many interesting towns after that.

11:31.000 --> 11:36.000
But I never saw men eat fire and snakes again.

11:37.000 --> 11:42.000
Then I went to bag that. What a wonderful city.

11:43.000 --> 11:45.000
But I was ill there.

11:46.000 --> 11:49.000
So I soon went back to Mecca.

11:50.000 --> 11:55.000
I learned from holy men and prayed there for a year.

11:56.000 --> 11:58.000
And slowly, I felt better.

11:59.000 --> 12:04.000
And what did you do next? I asked.

12:05.000 --> 12:08.000
I travelled by sea for the first time.

12:09.000 --> 12:12.000
It was my worst journey.

12:13.000 --> 12:14.000
He said.

12:15.000 --> 12:18.000
You can hear all about it tomorrow.

12:38.000 --> 12:43.000
Chapter Two. From Mecca to Chagatay.

12:44.000 --> 13:10.000
I arrived at my uncle's house early the next morning.

13:11.000 --> 13:17.000
So, where did you go on your first sea journey, uncle?

13:18.000 --> 13:19.000
I asked.

13:20.000 --> 13:22.000
Listen and learn.

13:23.000 --> 13:29.000
He said. And then he told me more of his story.

13:30.000 --> 13:37.000
After my first visit to Mecca, I wanted to see more of the world.

13:38.000 --> 13:43.000
So I travelled with friends to Jeddah on the Red Sea coast.

13:44.000 --> 13:47.000
And we sailed down to Yemen.

13:49.000 --> 13:52.000
For two days, the wind was behind us.

13:53.000 --> 13:56.000
But suddenly, it changed.

13:58.000 --> 14:01.000
The sea can be dangerous, unclean.

14:02.000 --> 14:05.000
One minute, it's beautifully quiet.

14:06.000 --> 14:09.000
And the next minute, it's dark and angry.

14:12.000 --> 14:18.000
The wind made our little ship go up and down in the water.

14:19.000 --> 14:21.000
And I felt very ill.

14:23.000 --> 14:29.000
When we stopped at a village on the coast, my friends and I got off.

14:30.000 --> 14:35.000
We finished our journey to the city of Aden by camel.

14:37.000 --> 14:45.000
There, we heard stories about a number of famous places in East Africa.

14:46.000 --> 14:52.000
So we got on a new ship and sailed down the African coast.

14:53.000 --> 14:58.000
Happily, I wasn't ill at all this time.

15:00.000 --> 15:09.000
After we visited different East African places, we sailed back to South Arabia some months later.

15:11.000 --> 15:17.000
Then, we wanted to visit Oman. So we took a ship there.

15:19.000 --> 15:24.000
But we got off it early, because we didn't like the sailors.

15:25.000 --> 15:32.000
This wasn't a good thing to do. I understood that later.

15:33.000 --> 15:40.000
My friend and I found a guide to take us on foot to Oman.

15:41.000 --> 15:45.000
I had a big bag of expensive clothes with me.

15:47.000 --> 15:51.000
So I gave it to the guide and he carried it.

15:52.000 --> 15:59.000
But after some time, the guide suddenly ran away with my bag.

16:00.000 --> 16:05.000
I went after him and I put my knife near his face.

16:06.000 --> 16:07.000
That stopped him.

16:08.000 --> 16:13.000
You must always look big and angry with bad men, Ahmed.

16:14.000 --> 16:15.000
Never forget that.

16:16.000 --> 16:22.000
The guide came back, but now I watched him day and night.

16:23.000 --> 16:28.000
He wanted to kill us, I think, and take our things.

16:29.000 --> 16:34.000
After a week of walking, we arrived in Oman.

16:35.000 --> 16:42.000
We were tired, hungry and thirsty, but happy to be alive.

16:42.000 --> 16:50.000
After Oman, I journeyed to the island of Bahrain.

16:51.000 --> 16:55.000
I saw young men in little ships there.

16:56.000 --> 17:00.000
Some of them weren't any older than you, Ahmed.

17:01.000 --> 17:10.000
They stood on the ships, looked down into the sea and then went far under the water for a very long time.

17:11.000 --> 17:16.000
When they came up, they had shells in their hands.

17:17.000 --> 17:21.000
They quickly opened the shells with their knives.

17:22.000 --> 17:24.000
And what was in them?

17:25.000 --> 17:31.000
Wonderful pearls, the biggest and most beautiful pearls in the world.

17:32.000 --> 17:37.000
People give a lot of money for them, you know.

17:38.000 --> 17:45.000
After Bahrain, I went back to the holy city of Mecca for a year.

17:46.000 --> 17:53.000
There, I heard interesting stories about the rich ruler of India.

17:54.000 --> 17:59.000
He gave work to judges from different countries, people said.

18:00.000 --> 18:05.000
So, I looked at different ways to travel to India.

18:05.000 --> 18:15.000
In the end, I went across country to Syria and then sailed up to Anatolia.

18:16.000 --> 18:22.000
There are sometimes big caravans to India from there, you see.

18:23.000 --> 18:28.000
I had a very nice journey across Anatolia.

18:29.000 --> 18:34.000
In every village, young men took us to a house for travelers.

18:35.000 --> 18:40.000
There, they gave us lots of good things to eat and drink.

18:41.000 --> 18:47.000
And when we left, all the people of the village cried and said, goodbye.

18:49.000 --> 18:52.000
I then journeyed north with some new friends.

18:53.000 --> 18:58.000
On the mountain roads, something strange happened.

18:59.000 --> 19:03.000
One afternoon, there was a lot of snow.

19:04.000 --> 19:10.000
And when I looked behind me, I couldn't find my way back to my friends.

19:11.000 --> 19:15.000
So I went on my horse to find help.

19:16.000 --> 19:21.000
After some time, I came to a dark little house.

19:23.000 --> 19:30.000
At the door, I spoke to an old man, but he couldn't understand me.

19:31.000 --> 19:34.000
So he called to a younger man.

19:35.000 --> 19:38.000
And when I saw him, I knew him.

19:39.000 --> 19:42.000
He was an old friend from home.

19:43.000 --> 19:45.000
What good luck!

19:45.000 --> 19:52.000
He helped me to find my new friends, and we stayed the night at his house.

19:53.000 --> 20:00.000
The holy man Burhan Adeen was right about meeting old friends on my travels.

20:01.000 --> 20:10.000
We then journeyed to the Black Sea, sailed across it, and traveled to the town of Al-Kiram.

20:11.000 --> 20:14.000
This was in green, open country.

20:15.000 --> 20:18.000
People called this place the step.

20:20.000 --> 20:23.000
There, we heard something exciting.

20:24.000 --> 20:30.000
The caravan of Rula Khan Osbegh was only three days away.

20:31.000 --> 20:37.000
It was a big city with shops, mosques, and places to eat in it.

20:37.000 --> 20:40.000
And it moved from place to place.

20:41.000 --> 20:45.000
I was interested to meet Khan Osbegh.

20:46.000 --> 20:52.000
He sat on a big chair, with his wife, by a lun, near him.

20:53.000 --> 20:55.000
She had a different caravan.

20:56.000 --> 21:06.000
We traveled with his caravan, and I learnt about by a lun, the daughter of the ruler of Constantinople.

21:07.000 --> 21:16.000
She wanted to visit her home city, so Khan Osbegh asked me, can you take her there?

21:17.000 --> 21:22.000
I was very happy to travel with by a lun's caravan.

21:23.000 --> 21:29.000
After 75 days, we arrived in Constantinople.

21:30.000 --> 21:36.000
I stayed for a month, and visited all the important places there.

21:37.000 --> 21:42.000
Then I began the long journey back to the step.

21:43.000 --> 21:49.000
It was now winter, a dark and dangerous time for step travelers.

21:50.000 --> 21:58.000
So I journeyed south to the country of Chagatay, and stayed with the ruler there.

21:59.000 --> 22:04.000
My uncle stopped, and began to close his eyes.

22:05.000 --> 22:10.000
And did you go to India? I asked.

22:12.000 --> 22:15.000
That's a story for tomorrow, Ahmed.

22:16.000 --> 22:17.000
He said.

22:35.000 --> 22:42.000
Chapter 3 from Chagatay to Calicut

22:42.000 --> 22:44.000
Chapter 3

23:03.000 --> 23:10.000
When I went back the next afternoon, my uncle was happy to see me.

23:11.000 --> 23:16.000
Ah, Ahmed, you're here again. Good.

23:17.000 --> 23:21.000
He smiled, and he began his story at once.

23:22.000 --> 23:36.000
For my long winter journey to India, the ruler of Chagatay gave me a warm coat, two horses, two camels, and lots of money.

23:37.000 --> 23:46.000
We traveled south to Samarkad, a city of beautiful buildings and wonderful gardens.

23:47.000 --> 23:52.000
From there, we journeyed to the Hindu Kush Mountains.

23:53.000 --> 23:59.000
Many people die in the snow in these famous mountains.

24:00.000 --> 24:05.000
So we stopped and waited for the bad weather to change.

24:06.000 --> 24:11.000
A good traveler always thinks about the weather, Ahmed.

24:12.000 --> 24:22.000
When it was better, we got up early one morning and went slowly over the cold and dangerous mountains.

24:23.000 --> 24:33.000
There was lots of snow under our feet, and we needed to put down coats for our big camels to walk on.

24:34.000 --> 24:39.000
We didn't want them to stop in the snow and die of cold.

24:40.000 --> 24:46.000
We were all very happy when the Hindu Kush Mountains were behind us.

24:48.000 --> 24:54.000
After four long months, we arrived in the north of India.

24:55.000 --> 24:59.000
And there, I saw something strange.

25:00.000 --> 25:07.000
We were on the road one day when a big animal came out from the trees.

25:08.000 --> 25:18.000
It had a fat body, little legs, and a very big head with a dangerous horn on it.

25:19.000 --> 25:26.000
The animal ran at my friend's horse and it hit the horse's leg with its horn.

25:30.000 --> 25:32.000
The horse nearly died.

25:33.000 --> 25:38.000
I later learnt the name of that strange animal.

25:39.000 --> 25:42.000
It was a rhinoceros.

25:43.000 --> 25:50.000
We journeyed to the city home of the Sultan of Delhi, Muhammad Tughlugh.

25:51.000 --> 25:56.000
I knew a lot about this man before I arrived.

25:56.000 --> 26:00.000
He liked judges from different countries.

26:01.000 --> 26:09.000
You see, Ahmad, Sultan's often need people from other countries to help them.

26:11.000 --> 26:15.000
I soon learnt more about the Sultan.

26:16.000 --> 26:23.000
It is very important to arrive in Delhi with expensive gifts for him.

26:24.000 --> 26:29.000
He then gives you back better gifts and lots of money.

26:30.000 --> 26:34.000
And in the end, you're richer than before.

26:36.000 --> 26:43.000
So, I got 30 beautiful horses and three camels for the Sultan.

26:44.000 --> 26:52.000
Remember that, Ahmad, when you meet a new ruler, always arrive with gifts.

26:54.000 --> 26:59.000
When we first came to Delhi, the Sultan was away.

27:00.000 --> 27:06.000
But when he heard about me, he made me one of his judges.

27:07.000 --> 27:11.000
I was now a rich and important man.

27:12.000 --> 27:18.000
I was, of course, excited to meet him when he arrived home.

27:19.000 --> 27:28.000
His house was very big and I needed to walk through door after door to find his room.

27:30.000 --> 27:36.000
He sat there on a gold chair with soldiers all about him.

27:37.000 --> 27:42.000
He took my hand and spoke warmly to me for some time.

27:42.000 --> 27:53.000
The next day, I went by horse with the Sultan and his soldiers through the streets of Delhi.

27:54.000 --> 27:58.000
Lots of men on elephants came after us.

27:59.000 --> 28:05.000
They left gold money on the road behind them when they went past.

28:06.000 --> 28:10.000
And people ran here and there to find it.

28:13.000 --> 28:21.000
The Sultan could write beautifully and he could speak four different languages.

28:22.000 --> 28:25.000
But he was often angry too.

28:26.000 --> 28:34.000
Every day, he asked his soldiers to kill people, sometimes for very little things.

28:35.000 --> 28:38.000
I needed to be very careful.

28:39.000 --> 28:43.000
For two years, my work went well.

28:44.000 --> 28:50.000
But then, the Sultan began to have trouble with his enemies.

28:51.000 --> 28:55.000
One ruler near Delhi fought with him.

28:56.000 --> 29:01.000
And what did the Sultan do with his enemy when he found the man?

29:02.000 --> 29:15.000
Well, Sultan Muhammad had lots of elephants and he took some of them and put big knives on their tusks.

29:16.000 --> 29:21.000
He then put his enemy in front of the elephants.

29:22.000 --> 29:25.000
The animals played with the man.

29:26.000 --> 29:32.000
They moved their knives up and down and cut his body open.

29:34.000 --> 29:40.000
He died, of course, and it was a very bad thing for us all to watch.

29:46.000 --> 29:53.000
I took a wife, a wonderful woman, to live with me in my house in Delhi.

29:55.000 --> 30:01.000
But then, my wife's father began to fight with the Sultan.

30:02.000 --> 30:08.000
This wasn't good because people began to speak badly about me.

30:09.000 --> 30:14.000
Perhaps I was an enemy of the Sultan too, they said.

30:15.000 --> 30:19.000
Then, something worse happened.

30:19.000 --> 30:27.000
A famous holy man, Sheikh Shihab ad-Din, lived on a hill near Delhi.

30:28.000 --> 30:35.000
I was very interested in him and I sometimes visited his home.

30:36.000 --> 30:43.000
But Sultan Muhammad was very angry with Sheikh Shihab ad-Din.

30:43.000 --> 30:53.000
He asked the holy man to do many different things, but Sheikh Shihab always said no to him.

30:54.000 --> 31:01.000
So in the end, the Sultan's men went and killed the holy man.

31:02.000 --> 31:10.000
And when the Sultan asked about the holy man's friends, people gave my name to him.

31:11.000 --> 31:19.000
Is Sultan Muhammad going to be angry with me? I thought, what can I do?

31:20.000 --> 31:28.000
I can't run away from him because then his soldiers are going to come and kill me too.

31:29.000 --> 31:35.000
I was very afraid. I stopped eating and drank only water.

31:36.000 --> 31:43.000
In the end, I left Delhi and stayed with a different holy man for five months.

31:44.000 --> 31:54.000
I gave away all my expensive things and beautiful clothes and I prayed from morning to night.

31:55.000 --> 32:05.000
Then, one day, the Sultan's soldiers came to visit me with horses and new clothes.

32:06.000 --> 32:17.000
The Sultan wants to see you, they said. I put on my new clothes, went back to Delhi and sat before the Sultan.

32:18.000 --> 32:27.000
Ibn Batuta, you're going to be my man in China. He smiled.

32:28.000 --> 32:41.000
I have fifteen Chinese visitors here. Go back to China with them and take gifts from me for their ruler.

32:42.000 --> 32:50.000
I couldn't say no to the Sultan. And of course, I wanted to see China.

32:51.000 --> 33:01.000
But very importantly, I could now leave the Sultan and stay alive. So I said yes at once.

33:02.000 --> 33:14.000
I left Delhi in a big caravan with gifts for the ruler of China, lots of horses and big bags of gold.

33:15.000 --> 33:24.000
My wife and young daughter came with me too. We had a thousand of the Sultan's best soldiers with us.

33:24.000 --> 33:33.000
That was good, because four days later, we met four thousand of the Sultan's enemies.

33:34.000 --> 33:40.000
We fought and killed them all, but I soon had more trouble.

33:41.000 --> 33:47.000
One afternoon, I went for a walk in the mountains far from the caravan.

33:47.000 --> 34:01.000
Suddenly, forty bandits came out from behind some rocks. They wanted to take all my expensive clothes from me, and to kill me too.

34:02.000 --> 34:11.000
Of course, I didn't want to die, so I told them lots of good stories, and I gave them all my clothes.

34:12.000 --> 34:20.000
In the morning, I was a free man, but I had nothing to wear, only my trousers.

34:21.000 --> 34:27.000
For days, I walked in the mountains with no body to help me.

34:28.000 --> 34:38.000
From time to time, I saw more bandits. But I went quickly behind rocks and trees, and they didn't see me.

34:39.000 --> 34:44.000
In the end, I was tired, cold, and hungry.

34:45.000 --> 34:52.000
One day, a good traveler found me, and he carried me to the next village.

34:53.000 --> 35:03.000
I had the best dinner in the world there, and it was wonderful to put on warm clothes too.

35:04.000 --> 35:08.000
Two days later, I found the caravan again.

35:09.000 --> 35:14.000
My wife and young daughter were very happy to see me.

35:16.000 --> 35:24.000
We journeyed to the town of Cambay, and carried all our beautiful gifts onto four ships.

35:25.000 --> 35:34.000
Then we sailed south to Calicut and put everything on three big Chinese ships there.

35:35.000 --> 35:41.000
I went to the mosque that afternoon and prayed for a good journey.

35:42.000 --> 35:49.000
But before I got on the ship, something very bad happened.

35:49.000 --> 35:58.000
The weather suddenly changed, and the wind broke two of our ships on rocks by the coast.

35:59.000 --> 36:06.000
We lost everything, the gifts, the people, and the animals.

36:07.000 --> 36:18.000
The third ship, with my wife and daughter on it, sailed away, and I never saw it or them again.

36:20.000 --> 36:28.000
I needed to go back to the Sultan and tell him about all this, but I was afraid.

36:29.000 --> 36:33.000
When the Sultan was angry, he often killed people.

36:34.000 --> 36:39.000
So, did you go back to Delhi uncle? I asked.

36:40.000 --> 36:45.000
You can hear about that, tomorrow, Ahmed.

36:46.000 --> 36:47.000
He smiled.

36:49.000 --> 36:52.000
This is the first time I've ever seen.

37:06.000 --> 37:08.000
Chapter 4

37:09.000 --> 37:12.000
From the Maldives to China

37:19.000 --> 37:41.000
My uncle didn't answer his door at once the next day, so I waited in the street.

37:42.000 --> 37:45.000
And I thought about the Sultan of Delhi.

37:45.000 --> 37:54.000
In my head, I could see his big angry face when he heard all about those three ships.

37:55.000 --> 37:59.000
Just then, my uncle opened the door.

38:01.000 --> 38:07.000
Ah! Hello, Ahmed. Come in and sit down.

38:08.000 --> 38:12.000
He said. And then he began his story again.

38:13.000 --> 38:25.000
Of course, I couldn't go back to the Sultan. That was dangerous. I needed to leave India at once. I knew.

38:26.000 --> 38:35.000
Then, I remembered the holy man, Burhan Adim's words about visiting China.

38:36.000 --> 38:43.000
Perhaps, I could go there alone without the Sultan's help.

38:44.000 --> 38:56.000
First, I sailed to the Maldives. They are truly wonderful islands, and there are about 2,000 of them.

38:57.000 --> 39:01.000
The Maldives are famous for their beautiful shells.

39:01.000 --> 39:10.000
The people there don't have gold money. For them, shells are money.

39:11.000 --> 39:24.000
I stayed on the island of Mali. I wanted only to visit the place, but the rulers there needed a new judge.

39:25.000 --> 39:31.000
When I arrived, they brought gifts of gold and pearls to my house.

39:32.000 --> 39:37.000
It wasn't easy for me to leave the island after that.

39:38.000 --> 39:46.000
So, I had new work to do. I was the judge on Mali.

39:47.000 --> 39:50.000
At first, everything went well.

39:51.000 --> 40:02.000
I took a wife from an important family, and I did my usual work. But I soon began to have enemies.

40:03.000 --> 40:11.000
I was a rich man, and people didn't like that. So, they said bad things about me.

40:13.000 --> 40:17.000
After 9 months, it was time to sail away.

40:18.000 --> 40:26.000
My wife wasn't a good sea traveler, so I left her behind on the island.

40:27.000 --> 40:35.000
You sometimes need to leave a place quickly, Ahmed, before things go badly wrong.

40:36.000 --> 40:43.000
I left for China, but first I sailed to the island of Serendip.

40:44.000 --> 40:53.000
When we were 9 days away from it, we could see its famous mountain, Adam's mountain, across the sea.

40:54.000 --> 41:06.000
Many people make the pilgrimage to this holy mountain, because on it, you can see a footprint of Adam, the first man in our world.

41:07.000 --> 41:12.000
I stayed with the Sultan of Serendip for three days.

41:13.000 --> 41:21.000
He loved listening to my traveler's stories, and he gave me pearls and big rubies.

41:22.000 --> 41:26.000
Serendip is famous for its rubies, you see.

41:27.000 --> 41:32.000
The women there, wear them all over their arms and legs.

41:33.000 --> 41:38.000
The Sultan told me all about Adam's mountain.

41:39.000 --> 41:47.000
There are two ways to walk up to Adam's footprint, an easy way and a dangerous way.

41:48.000 --> 41:53.000
You're a true pilgrim, only when you go the dangerous way.

41:54.000 --> 41:58.000
So, of course, I went up that way.

41:59.000 --> 42:05.000
It was a long journey over big rocks and between dark trees.

42:06.000 --> 42:10.000
But we arrived in the end at Adam's footprint.

42:11.000 --> 42:13.000
It was wonderful there.

42:14.000 --> 42:20.000
You're up in the sky, and you can see things very far away.

42:21.000 --> 42:26.000
After that, I left Serendip by ship for India.

42:27.000 --> 42:33.000
I was a happy man, with lots of pearls and rubies in my bag.

42:34.000 --> 42:37.000
But soon, things went wrong.

42:38.000 --> 42:43.000
One day, sudden winds took our ship onto some rocks.

42:44.000 --> 42:47.000
I was afraid, because I can't swim.

42:47.000 --> 42:52.000
The sailors took some of the women travelers away.

42:53.000 --> 42:58.000
But I stayed alone all night on the ship and prayed.

42:59.000 --> 43:06.000
In the morning, some people found me and took me back to the coast of Serendip.

43:07.000 --> 43:14.000
I sailed away once more, but this time, lots of pirates came onto our ship.

43:14.000 --> 43:19.000
They took all my pearls, rubies and expensive clothes,

43:19.000 --> 43:24.000
and then left me on an island in only my trousers.

43:25.000 --> 43:28.000
Not again, I thought.

43:29.000 --> 43:37.000
I sailed back to the Maldives once more, and there, I got on a ship to China.

43:38.000 --> 43:43.000
On the journey, I stopped at the sea.

43:44.000 --> 43:52.000
I stopped at a number of places, and visited two islands, Sumatra and Java.

43:53.000 --> 43:56.000
Java was very interesting.

43:57.000 --> 44:03.000
Everybody there has an elephant, and people visit the shops on them.

44:04.000 --> 44:13.000
After Java, we sailed for 40 days with a good wind behind us and arrived in China.

44:14.000 --> 44:18.000
There's a lot to tell you about China, Ackman.

44:19.000 --> 44:23.000
Chinese people can make many different things very well,

44:24.000 --> 44:28.000
from wonderful pictures to beautiful boxes.

44:29.000 --> 44:33.000
China is a very nice country for travelers,

44:34.000 --> 44:38.000
and I journeyed easily from town to town.

44:39.000 --> 44:43.000
Some of their animals are different from our animals, too.

44:44.000 --> 44:46.000
That interested me.

44:47.000 --> 44:52.000
They have cats with blue, green eyes, you know.

44:53.000 --> 45:00.000
And when I stopped in one city called Fuju, something very interesting happened.

45:01.000 --> 45:07.000
A judge arrived in the city, and my friends took me to meet him.

45:08.000 --> 45:13.000
We said, hello, and then this man looked at me, and I looked at him.

45:14.000 --> 45:17.000
I know you, I cried.

45:18.000 --> 45:25.000
You're Al Busri, and you're from Seyuta, not far from my hometown of Tangier.

45:26.000 --> 45:29.000
That's right, he smiled.

45:30.000 --> 45:33.000
We laughed and talked for hours.

45:34.000 --> 45:38.000
You meet people in the strangest places, Ackman.

45:39.000 --> 45:47.000
The holy man, Burhan al-Din, was right again about finding old friends on my journeys.

45:49.000 --> 45:55.000
After some months in China, I was ready to begin my long journey home.

45:57.000 --> 46:00.000
So, I went to look for a ship.

46:01.000 --> 46:05.000
And did you come home at once, I asked?

46:06.000 --> 46:08.000
No, he said.

46:09.000 --> 46:16.000
I stopped at cities from my earlier journeys, Damascus, Cairo, and many more.

46:17.000 --> 46:23.000
But when I went back, they were dark and different places.

46:24.000 --> 46:25.000
He said slowly.

46:26.000 --> 46:29.000
I can tell you all about that, tomorrow.

46:35.000 --> 46:53.000
Chapter 5, to Tangier and Granada.

47:05.000 --> 47:20.000
What was the trouble with those cities when you visited them again?

47:21.000 --> 47:24.000
I asked my uncle when I arrived the next day.

47:25.000 --> 47:29.000
Let's talk about my journey from China first.

47:30.000 --> 47:32.000
He answered quietly.

47:33.000 --> 47:38.000
On my way back from China, I stopped in Sumatra again.

47:39.000 --> 47:46.000
Then, I got on a big ship and sailed for 40 days to India.

47:48.000 --> 47:53.000
When I arrived there, I thought about visiting the Sultan.

47:54.000 --> 47:55.000
But I was afraid.

47:56.000 --> 48:03.000
Perhaps he remembered his gifts for the ruler of China and the time when I lost them all.

48:04.000 --> 48:09.000
From India, I sailed to the south coast of Arabia.

48:10.000 --> 48:14.000
I then traveled through Persia to Baghdad.

48:15.000 --> 48:17.000
I journeyed across the desert.

48:18.000 --> 48:24.000
And in the end, I arrived once more in the city of Damascus.

48:25.000 --> 48:29.000
It was 20 years from the time of my last visit.

48:30.000 --> 48:32.000
But I remembered it well.

48:34.000 --> 48:38.000
In Damascus, I heard something interesting.

48:39.000 --> 48:44.000
A teacher from Tangier now lived and worked in the city.

48:45.000 --> 48:52.000
I was excited to meet this man, and I asked him at once for news from home.

48:53.000 --> 48:55.000
My father was dead.

48:56.000 --> 48:59.000
But my mother was alive, he told me.

49:01.000 --> 49:03.000
I felt bad about my father.

49:04.000 --> 49:14.000
And suddenly, after 24 long years away, I began to think of going back home and of seeing my mother.

49:16.000 --> 49:18.000
I journeyed to Aleppo.

49:19.000 --> 49:22.000
But there, I heard some bad news.

49:23.000 --> 49:28.000
The plague wasn't far away, and many people were ill with it.

49:29.000 --> 49:35.000
At first, I traveled quickly from city to city in Syria.

49:36.000 --> 49:40.000
I wanted to stay in front of the plague, you see.

49:41.000 --> 49:49.000
But after a time, when I arrived in new places, the plague was there before me.

49:51.000 --> 49:54.000
So, I went back to Damascus.

49:56.000 --> 49:58.000
Here, I learnt the worst.

49:59.000 --> 50:06.000
At that time, lots of men, women and children died of plague there every day.

50:07.000 --> 50:13.000
Everybody came out into the streets with their holy books and prayed for their families.

50:14.000 --> 50:17.000
But nobody could stop the plague.

50:19.000 --> 50:24.000
The news of the plague made me think of my mother again.

50:25.000 --> 50:28.000
Was she ill too, perhaps?

50:29.000 --> 50:33.000
So, I traveled on pilgrimage to Mecca one more time.

50:33.000 --> 50:38.000
And then began my way back home through Cairo.

50:39.000 --> 50:44.000
Of course, I knew this wonderful city from years before.

50:45.000 --> 50:48.000
But it was very different now.

50:49.000 --> 50:55.000
21,000 people died from the plague there every day.

50:56.000 --> 51:01.000
My uncle stopped and looked out of the window.

51:02.000 --> 51:06.000
Did you get ill, uncle? I asked.

51:07.000 --> 51:09.000
No, I didn't.

51:10.000 --> 51:12.000
He said slowly.

51:13.000 --> 51:16.000
And I thank God for that.

51:17.000 --> 51:23.000
I left Cairo, traveled to Tunis, and then got on a ship.

51:23.000 --> 51:27.000
And then got on a ship to the island of Sardinia.

51:28.000 --> 51:30.000
We didn't stay there long.

51:31.000 --> 51:36.000
There were bandits on the island, and they wanted to fight and kill us.

51:37.000 --> 51:39.000
So we left quickly.

51:40.000 --> 51:48.000
After Sardinia, I sailed to North Africa, and then traveled by donkey to Tangier.

51:49.000 --> 51:56.000
But not long before I arrived home, I heard bad news about my mother.

51:57.000 --> 52:02.000
She was dead, people in the town of Tarza told me.

52:03.000 --> 52:06.000
I was very sorry to hear this.

52:07.000 --> 52:13.000
In the end, I went to the most important city in our country, Fez.

52:14.000 --> 52:18.000
And I met our ruler, Sultan Abu Inan there.

52:20.000 --> 52:25.000
To me, he was more wonderful than all the rulers in the world.

52:26.000 --> 52:31.000
Sometimes, Ahmad, the things in your home country are the best.

52:33.000 --> 52:39.000
After that, I went back to Tangier and visited my mother's grave.

52:40.000 --> 52:42.000
I was ill for three months.

52:43.000 --> 52:50.000
But then, I heard my friends talk about trouble in the Kingdom of Granada.

52:51.000 --> 52:52.000
Al-Andalus.

52:54.000 --> 53:00.000
King Alfonso of Castile is going to fight our brothers there.

53:01.000 --> 53:04.000
They said, we must help them.

53:04.000 --> 53:06.000
We must help them.

53:08.000 --> 53:13.000
Soon after that, we sailed to the Kingdom of Granada.

53:14.000 --> 53:22.000
But King Alfonso died of the plague before we arrived, and we didn't need to fight.

53:23.000 --> 53:29.000
So I stayed and visited all the interesting places in that country.

53:30.000 --> 53:35.000
Now, I must tell you a story about my time there.

53:36.000 --> 53:44.000
One day, I was on the coast road to Malaga, when I met twelve soldiers on horses.

53:46.000 --> 53:52.000
They asked me to journey with them, because the road to Malaga was dangerous.

53:53.000 --> 53:56.000
There were enemy ships near the coast.

53:57.000 --> 54:05.000
I wanted to go with them, but in the end, I stayed behind and travelled with my friends.

54:06.000 --> 54:13.000
Later, on the road to Malaga, we found a dead horse in our way.

54:14.000 --> 54:21.000
It was one of the twelve soldiers' horses, and I soon learnt their story.

54:22.000 --> 54:28.000
Those soldiers were now in the hands of dangerous enemy sailors.

54:29.000 --> 54:31.000
But I was free.

54:32.000 --> 54:38.000
I thanked God for that, and I prayed for all of our brothers.

54:40.000 --> 54:45.000
Then, I journeyed to the famous city of Granada.

54:46.000 --> 54:51.000
In one of the beautiful gardens there, I met some writers.

54:52.000 --> 54:55.000
They were interested in my traveller's stories.

54:56.000 --> 55:04.000
And one young man, Ibn Josai, listened carefully and began to write about my long journey.

55:05.000 --> 55:13.000
I didn't know it at the time, but Ibn Josai was later a very important friend to me.

55:16.000 --> 55:23.000
Soon after that, I left the Kingdom of Granada and sailed back to Morocco.

55:24.000 --> 55:28.000
And this time you stayed at home in our country.

55:29.000 --> 55:33.000
Is that right, Uncle? I said.

55:34.000 --> 55:36.000
Well, no.

55:37.000 --> 55:38.000
He smiled.

55:38.000 --> 55:39.000
I didn't.

55:40.000 --> 55:43.000
There was one more country to visit.

55:43.000 --> 55:49.000
A place of hot deserts and dangerous snakes.

55:50.000 --> 55:55.000
Come back to hear about that tomorrow morning, Ahmed.

56:14.000 --> 56:19.000
Chapter 6, Tamali and Back

56:20.000 --> 56:46.000
When I arrived the next day, my uncle said,

56:46.000 --> 56:50.000
Ahmed, you wanted to be a traveller before.

56:51.000 --> 56:53.000
Do you want to be a traveller now?

56:54.000 --> 56:57.000
Yes, I answered.

56:58.000 --> 57:04.000
It's not easy, I know, but I truly want to travel.

57:05.000 --> 57:07.000
Good, he said.

57:08.000 --> 57:12.000
So listen carefully, because there's more to learn.

57:12.000 --> 57:21.000
For my last journey, I travelled south, because I wanted to visit Mali.

57:22.000 --> 57:37.000
You see, years before in Cairo, I heard many stories about the famous king of Mali, Mansa Suleiman, and all his gold.

57:38.000 --> 57:47.000
So, I left Fez and journeyed across the Atlas Mountains to the town of Sijilmasa.

57:48.000 --> 57:54.000
Now, do you remember, I met a man called Al-Bushri in China?

57:55.000 --> 58:01.000
Well, in Sijilmasa, I met Al-Bushri's brother.

58:02.000 --> 58:04.000
It was strange.

58:04.000 --> 58:14.000
The two brothers were in very different places, but I met the older one and the younger one.

58:15.000 --> 58:21.000
Then I travelled by camel, with a caravan, to Terraza.

58:22.000 --> 58:27.000
It wasn't a beautiful village, but it had some interesting buildings.

58:28.000 --> 58:35.000
The people there take big pieces of salt from the desert and make houses with them.

58:36.000 --> 58:39.000
There's a salt mosque there, too.

58:40.000 --> 58:49.000
I stayed in a little salt house in the village, but the water there was very bad to drink.

58:50.000 --> 59:00.000
So, after ten days, we left and began our long and dangerous journey south across the hot desert.

59:01.000 --> 59:10.000
At first, a friend and I left our caravan every morning to look for things to eat for our camels.

59:11.000 --> 59:15.000
But one day, we heard some bad news.

59:16.000 --> 59:25.000
Ibn Ziri, a man from our caravan, walked alone into the desert with no water bottle.

59:26.000 --> 59:30.000
Later, friends found him dead under a tree.

59:32.000 --> 59:36.000
After that, we always stayed with the caravan.

59:37.000 --> 59:41.000
You must never go alone into the desert, Ahmed.

59:42.000 --> 59:48.000
You can easily forget your way and die quickly in the hot sun.

59:50.000 --> 59:54.000
There were lots of big snakes in this desert, too.

59:55.000 --> 59:59.000
And one man in the caravan liked playing with them.

01:00:00.000 --> 01:00:01.000
What happened to him?

01:00:02.000 --> 01:00:08.000
A snake put its teeth into one of his fingers one morning and he nearly died.

01:00:09.000 --> 01:00:16.000
In the end, with a knife, he cut this finger from his hand, and so he lived.

01:00:17.000 --> 01:00:23.000
Remember, playing with snakes is very dangerous.

01:00:25.000 --> 01:00:33.000
We journeyed for many weeks to the biggest city in Mali, to meet King Mansa Suleiman.

01:00:33.000 --> 01:00:42.000
But soon after we arrived, I ate something bad, and I was ill for a long time.

01:00:43.000 --> 01:00:53.000
Usually, when you're an important traveler, the ruler takes expensive gifts to you when you first arrive in a town.

01:00:54.000 --> 01:01:02.000
So, I waited in my bed day after day for Mansa Suleiman's men to visit me.

01:01:04.000 --> 01:01:08.000
After some weeks, the king's men arrived with gifts.

01:01:09.000 --> 01:01:15.000
Perhaps it was some nice clothes or some pieces of gold, I thought.

01:01:16.000 --> 01:01:17.000
But no!

01:01:18.000 --> 01:01:21.000
They gave me some old bread and meat.

01:01:24.000 --> 01:01:30.000
When I felt better, I visited the king's beautiful house every day.

01:01:31.000 --> 01:01:35.000
I waited for more gifts, but I got nothing.

01:01:36.000 --> 01:01:39.000
In the end, I spoke to the king.

01:01:41.000 --> 01:01:43.000
I'm a world traveler.

01:01:44.000 --> 01:01:49.000
In every country, rulers give me wonderful gifts when I arrive.

01:01:50.000 --> 01:01:58.000
I arrived in your city four months ago, but you do not speak to me or give me nice things.

01:01:59.000 --> 01:02:02.000
What can I say about you to other people?

01:02:05.000 --> 01:02:07.000
Things soon changed after that.

01:02:09.000 --> 01:02:17.000
Mansa Suleiman was now very good to me, and he gave me a house and a lot of gold.

01:02:19.000 --> 01:02:27.000
And when I left the city with a friend to visit the country, his men brought me more gold.

01:02:28.000 --> 01:02:33.000
In the end, my friend and I came to a big river.

01:02:34.000 --> 01:02:46.000
I saw some very strange animals in the water there, horses with big fat bodies, little legs and elephants feet.

01:02:47.000 --> 01:02:54.000
My friend called them hippopotamuses, but they were new to me.

01:02:56.000 --> 01:03:05.000
I traveled north to Timbuktu, but in a town near Timbuktu, I was very ill once more.

01:03:06.000 --> 01:03:11.000
Then one day, I got a letter from the Sultan of Morocco.

01:03:12.000 --> 01:03:14.000
He needed me at once.

01:03:14.000 --> 01:03:17.000
What does he want? I thought.

01:03:18.000 --> 01:03:24.000
We traveled north for a long time and went back over the Atlas Mountains.

01:03:25.000 --> 01:03:32.000
The winter snow there made the roads very dangerous, and we journeyed slowly.

01:03:34.000 --> 01:03:41.000
In the end, after some months, I arrived back at the Sultan's home in Fez.

01:03:41.000 --> 01:03:48.000
I have important work for you, he said, when he saw me.

01:03:49.000 --> 01:04:01.000
There's a young writer here. His name is Ibn Jusai, and he wants to write down all your stories.

01:04:02.000 --> 01:04:06.000
Then everybody can learn about them.

01:04:07.000 --> 01:04:15.000
Ibn Jusai, I said at once. I know him. I met him in Granada.

01:04:16.000 --> 01:04:22.000
A holy man once told me about meeting friends in different places.

01:04:23.000 --> 01:04:27.000
It happened before, and now it's happening again.

01:04:29.000 --> 01:04:34.000
Of course, it was wonderful to speak to Ibn Jusai again.

01:04:34.000 --> 01:04:45.000
I told him all about the exciting places, the different animals, and the interesting people from all my journeys.

01:04:46.000 --> 01:04:52.000
And now, Ahmed, all these stories are in a book.

01:04:53.000 --> 01:05:02.000
I'm not going to be here always, but take this. It's my gift to you.

01:05:02.000 --> 01:05:10.000
You can read it and learn more about my travels when you want.

01:05:11.000 --> 01:05:17.000
With that, my uncle put a big book into my hand.

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:22.000
Thank you, uncle, I said.

01:05:23.000 --> 01:05:27.000
I took the book home with me that afternoon.

01:05:28.000 --> 01:05:31.000
My uncle died not long after that.

01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:40.000
But I have his book, and I often read it to this day.

